   "source": [
    "# System Identification with the ``ssid`` package"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from ssid.utilities.printing import *\n",
    "from ssid.utilities.testing import test_method\n",
    "from ssid.utilities.config import Config\n",
    "import ssid\n",
    "from ssid import modal, spec\n",
    "from control import ss, forced_response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Define a SDOF system\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "m  | mass\n",
    "k  | stiffness\n",
    "c  | damping coefficient\n",
    "nt | number of timesteps\n",
    "dt | timestep"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![sdof](./figures/sdof.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "natural period: 1.1471s\n",
      "damping ratio: 0.01\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# parameters of SDOF system\n",
    "mass = 1       # mass\n",
    "k = 30         # stiffness\n",
    "zeta = 0.01    # damping ratio\n",
    "omega_n = np.sqrt(k/mass)  # natural frequency (rad/s)\n",
    "Tn = 2*np.pi/omega_n  # natural periods (s)\n",
    "c = 2*zeta*mass*omega_n    # damping coefficient\n",
    "print(f\"natural period: {Tn:<3.5}s\")\n",
    "print(f\"damping ratio: {zeta}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# forcing frequencies (rad/s)\n",
    "omega_f = [0.017*omega_n, 0.14*omega_n, 0.467*omega_n, 0.186*omega_n, 0.2937*omega_n]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# forcing function (input)\n",
    "nt = 5000       # number of timesteps\n",
    "dt = 0.03       # timestep\n",
    "tf = nt*dt      # final time\n",
    "t = np.arange(start = 0, stop = tf, step = dt)\n",
    "f = np.sum(np.sin([omega*t for omega in omega_f]), axis=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# displacement response (analytical solution) (output)\n",
    "omega_D = omega_n*np.sqrt(1-zeta**2)\n",
    "y = np.zeros((len(omega_f),nt))\n",
    "for i,omega in enumerate(omega_f):\n",
    "    C3 = (1/k)*(1-(omega/omega_n)**2)/((1-(omega/omega_n)**2)**2+(2*zeta*omega/omega_n))**2\n",
    "    C4 = -(2*zeta*omega/omega_n)*(1-(omega/omega_n)**2)/((1-(omega/omega_n)**2)**2+(2*zeta*omega/omega_n))**2\n",
    "    C1 = -C4\n",
    "    C2 = (zeta*omega_n*C1-omega*C3)/omega_D\n",
    "    y[i,:] = np.exp(-zeta*omega_n*t)*(C1*np.cos(omega_D*t)+C2*np.sin(omega_D*t)) + C3*np.sin(omega*t) + C4*np.cos(omega*t)\n",
    "y = np.sum(y,axis=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot input vs. output\n",
    "plot_io(inputs=f, outputs=y, t=t, title=\"SDOF Displacement Response to Sinusoidal Forcing\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Perform System Identification"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Transfer Function Methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Set parameters\n",
    "conf = Config()\n",
    "conf.damping = zeta\n",
    "conf.period_band = (0.01,3) # Period band (s)\n",
    "\n",
    "# A place to store models and their predictions\n",
    "transfer_models = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate a transfer function representation of the system\n",
    "transfer_models[\"Fourier Transform\"] = spec.fourier_transfer(inputs=f, outputs=y, step=dt, **conf)\n",
    "transfer_models[\"Response Spectrum\"] = spec.response_transfer(inputs=f, outputs=y, step=dt, pseudo=False, threads=8, periods=(*conf.period_band, 500), **conf)\n",
    "plot_transfer(transfer_models, title=\"Transfer Functions\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Determing the fundamental frequency\n",
    "fundamental_fourier = modal.spectrum_modes(*transfer_models[\"Fourier Transform\"])\n",
    "fundamental_response = modal.spectrum_modes(*transfer_models[\"Response Spectrum\"])\n",
    "plt.vlines([fundamental_fourier[0], fundamental_response[0]],ymin=[0,0],ymax=[fundamental_fourier[1],fundamental_response[1]],linestyles='--',colors='k',label=\"identified natural period\")\n",
    "plt.text(fundamental_fourier[0],fundamental_fourier[1],r\"$T_{1}$ = \"+str(np.round(fundamental_fourier[0][0],3)))\n",
    "plt.text(fundamental_response[0],fundamental_response[1],r\"$T_{1}$ = \"+str(fundamental_response[0][0]))\n",
    "# plt.vlines([2*np.pi/f for f in omega_f],0,0.5,color=\"r\",label=\"forcing periods\")\n",
    "plt.xlim(conf.period_band)\n",
    "plt.legend();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### State Space Methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|█████████▉| 4700/4701 [00:00<00:00, 63638.07it/s]"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Spectral quantities:\n",
      "       T(s)        ζ        EMACO        MPC     EMACO*MPC          T % error    ζ % error\n",
      "      1.147      0.01       1.0        1.0        1.0          -2.516e-13    3.105e-12\n",
      "Mean Period(s): 1.1471474419090923\n",
      "Standard Dev(s): 0.0\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate a state space realization of the system\n",
    "A,B,C,D = ssid.system(inputs=f, outputs=y, r=2)\n",
    "# Obtain natural period and damping ratio from the state space model\n",
    "ss_modes = modal.system_modes((A,B,C,D),dt,outlook=190)\n",
    "print_modes(ss_modes, Tn=Tn, zeta=zeta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Reproduce the response with the state space model\n",
    "y_ssid = forced_response(ss(A,B,C,D,dt), T=t, U=f, squeeze=False, return_x=False).outputs\n",
    "plot_pred(ytrue=y, models=y_ssid, t=t, title=\"System ID Predicted Displacement Response\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Breakdown of State Space Methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### General Parameters\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`p ` | number of output channels\n",
    "`q ` | number of input channels\n",
    "`nt` | number of timesteps\n",
    "`dt` | timestep\n",
    "`d`  | decimation (downsampling) factor\n",
    "`r`, `order` | model order (2 times number of DOF)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to Observer Kalman Identification (OKID)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`m`  | number of Markov parameters to compute (at most = nt)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to Eigensystem Realization Algorithm (ERA)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`no`, `horizon` | number of observability parameters, or prediction horizon\n",
    "`nc` | number of controllability parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to Data Correlations (DC)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`a`  | (alpha) number of additional block rows in Hankel matrix of correlation matrices\n",
    "`b`  | (beta) number of additional block columns in Hankel matrix of correlation matrices\n",
    "`l`  | initial lag\n",
    "`g`  | lag (gap) between correlations\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to System Realization with Information Matrix (SRIM)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`no`, `horizon` | number of steps used for identification, or prediction horizon"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Parameters for Mode Validation\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`outlook` | number of steps used for temporal consistency in EMAC"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Method Inputs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set parameters\n",
    "conf = Config()\n",
    "conf.m  = 500\n",
    "conf.no = 240\n",
    "conf.nc = 240\n",
    "conf.r  =   2\n",
    "conf.a  =   0\n",
    "conf.b  =   0\n",
    "conf.l  =  10\n",
    "conf.g  =   3\n",
    "\n",
    "# A place to store models and their predictions\n",
